Automatic module is a jar file which does not have module-info.java. Which means legacy jar files. But other important thing is that it is added to MODULE PATH. So it is treated as a module with the same name as jar file, or a name given in manifest file.&lt;br&gt;
Also, in comparison, all the code and jars in CLASSPATH get added to UNNAMED module!&lt;br&gt;
Both implicitly export all public stuff, and implicitly imports all public stuff from other modules.

