For this, instead of maintaining interval variables, you can simply use binary search. If for the current value, sum of `n` natural numbers till current number greater than `J`, go left, else, go on the right side(as in, go for a larger number).

    public class Main {
        public static void main(String[] args) {
          int J = 39;
          int low = 0, high = J;
          int ans = -1;
          while(low &lt;= high){
            int mid = low + ((high - low) / 2);
            int valJ = mid * (mid + 1) / 2;
            if(valJ &gt; J){
              high = mid - 1;
            }else{
              ans = mid;
              low = mid + 1;
            }
          }
          
          System.out.println(J + &quot; -&gt; &quot; + ans);
      }
    }

